At the moment, if you import a XML file from different versions, you only receive a generic warning message that the importing has failed so we need to investigate the customer logs. 

Some customers sometimes are not aware about their production version, and need to check with the support why their XML export is failing while importing it in a staging instance.

It would be nice if Confluence could compare the XML between versions and inform in the U.I that you are trying to import a file from a previous/later version or if the file version was checked before upgrading.

