I've come across a handful of customers who upgrade Confluence across major versions using XML backups, and they run into problems, which is expected.

As we do on [Restoring a Site|https://confluence.atlassian.com/doc/restoring-a-site-152034.html], I think it'd be a good idea to include the same warning against using XML backups for upgrades on the [Upgrading Confluence|https://confluence.atlassian.com/doc/upgrading-confluence-4578.html] document.

