This is a feature request to provide the user a warning in case of importing a space with illegal characters in its KEY. The warning would be related to either advice the user to not import it or just a message saying that it cannot be imported due to the content on its KEY.

For example, let's suppose that the Space key was manually changed in the DB using a illegal character (not included under A-Z / 0-9) and then, tried to import in Confluence. The space will be imported, but, it will not be functional since this is using the unexpected character.

